SUMMARY:Echoes of the Maihar Tradition
DESCRIPTION:A concert of emotional connection to the timeless beauty of the monsoon ragas. \nThis evening\, sarod exponents Shiraz Ali Khan and Dwiptanil Bhattacharjee\, accompanied by tabla artist Mainak Biswas\, present a sarod duet. The conversation between two artists of the Maihar Senia Gharana unfolds as they explore the many shades of a Malhaar raga: from the meditative expansiveness of the aalap to the vibrant rhythmic dialogue with tabla in the concluding section. \nThe monsoon has inspired generations of musicians\, poets\, and artists across India. This concert revisits that tradition\, celebrating the expressive power of the Malhaar ragas and the depth\, imagination\, and emotional resonance that define this musical lineage. \nSupported by: \n \n\n\nA Sarod Duet\nRSVP here (https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfMnyj3nBkOdvSbI6j0BxN1LdDbq1XDDDah1xmbw6_4QxcwzA/viewform?usp=publish-editor)\n*Performers*: Shiraz Ali Khan\, Dwiptanil Bhattacharjee\, Mainak Biswas\n*Event Categories*: Music\, Performing Arts
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/echoes-of-the-maihar-tradition/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Music,Performing Arts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/Thumbnail-5.jpg
