SUMMARY:J’ai Un Bleu | I Have A Bruise
DESCRIPTION:J’ai un Bleu is a female-led dance performance based on a collection of interviews from women and activists\, made by WomanEwer in 2021. The work addresses womanhood from the sensitive issues and challenges to the celebration of survival and strength. The performance will be followed by a Q&A session with the audience. What happens when woman across the world are given a platform for their voices? \nDirected by Laura Kenyon in collaboration with the dancers in London\, the piece originally toured in the UK\, France\, Mexico and India. This performance is a culmination of the nine day long Dance Residency that was held in the BIC premises with a group of eight dancers\, inspired by their own stories of womanhood\, struggle and success. \nSupported by: \n \n\n\nThe Culminating Performance of the WomanEwer Dance Residency\nAges 18+\nRSVP here (https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfZ-KAo1NtI8ASNr_8H7wB2v24t1cB0SX55lk3ei8rmALyjeg/viewform?usp=publish-editor)\n*Performers*: Laura Kenyon\, Sara Maurizi\, Akshiti Roychowdhury\, Rashmi Mali\, Aswathy Chandran\, Greeshma Narendran\, Prakriti Sharma\, Tanaya Nair\, Henna Raisinghani\, Seher Noor Mehra\n*Event Categories*: Dance\, Gender\, Performing Arts
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/jai-un-bleu-i-have-a-bruise/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Dance,Gender,Performing Arts
